<h1>Call for Demonstrations</h1>
<p><a href="ICME_Call_for_Demos.pdf" target="_blank">PDF Version</a> of this Call for Demonstrations and Application Form</p>
<p>ICME 2003 will host one demonstration session on each day of the conference, July 7, 8 & 9, 2003. The goal
of the demonstration sessions is to allow members of the multimedia community an opportunity to demonstrate
working multimedia systems. This environment allows conference participants to view demonstrations firsthand
in a manner not possible in a technical talk or poster session alone. We request proposals for demonstrations
from anyone in the multimedia community, including researchers, academic institutions, research labs, and
industry.</p>
<p>The demonstration sessions will be held in the exhibit hall / poster area of the conference. Each demonstration
will be allotted a three-hour time slot (to coincide with the poster session timing). Each demonstration area
will have a 4 foot by 8 foot posterboard as a backdrop with a table in front of the area with power available, if
requested. We suggest that participants bring a poster to the session to support their demonstration. We would
like for the demonstrations to be 10 to 30 minutes in length, and that the demonstration be presented several
times during the three hour session. This will allow people the time to observe several demonstrations. Please
visit the ICME 2003 website <a href="http://www.icme2003.com"><b>www.icme2003.com</b></a> for the most current information on the demonstration
sessions.</p>
<p>Demonstrations submitted by April 18, 2003 <em>(Extended)</em> will be allotted 2 pdf pages on the CDROM proceedings; those
demonstrations submitted after April 18, 2003 <em>(Extended)</em> will not be given space in the proceedings.</p>
